The presidency has announced when President Muhammadu Buhari will air the New Year broadcast to Nigerians. Garba Shehu, the President’s Spokesman, said Buhari would make a New Year broadcast to the nation Friday, January 1, 2021 at 7 am. Shehu disclosed this in a tweet via his Twitter account on Thursday. The tweet read, “President Muhammadu Buhari will make a New Year broadcast to the nation Friday, January 1, 2021, at 7 am. “Television, radio and other electronic media outlets are enjoined to join the network services of the Nigerian Television Authority (NTA) and Federal Radio Corporation of Nigeria (FRCN) respectively, for the broadcast.” <img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-861244 size-full" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/garba-shehu.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="250" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/garba-shehu.jpg 601w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/garba-shehu-300x125.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 601px) 100vw, 601px">